{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_data_ver01/data/sn87055779/00517016998/1924041601/0244.xml":{"full_text":"FLAYS PESSIMISTS\nIN ADDRESS BEFORE\nCOMMERCE CHAMBER\n\nBusiness What One Makes It\n\u2014Advertising Surest Way\nto Get It, Dictum.\nBusiness pessimists were flayed;\nadvertising was extolled; and four\nyears of excellent business condi\ntions were predicted by James F.\nPotts, sales manager of the Beck\nwith Corp, who spoke to Misha\nwaka Chamber of Commerce mem\nbers at their monthly luncheon\nTuesday noon In Hotel Mishawaka.\n\"Business Is what you make It!\u201d\nthe speaker from Dowagiac, Mich.,\nexclaimed. \"Financial conditions\ntoday are as sound as at any time In\nthe history of the country and If\nbusiness doesn\u2019t suit us now, what\nare we going to do? Take a tip from\nBill Wrigiey and advertise!\"\nAlthough Mr. Potts' address was\ncalled \"The Business Outlook,\" he\ndid not go Into a maze of technical\nlfs and wherefores. Instead, in\nplain American business-man lan\nguage he drove home the point that\noptimism must be the rule and en\nthusiasm the law if the present day\nbusiness man expects to succeed.\nPessimism Ruins Business.\n\"Pessimistic talk, gentlemen, will\nImmediately ruin any business,\u201d the\nspeaker declared. \u201cUse Detroit as\nan example; for years the pessimists\nhave been predicting dire destruction\nfor that city. The optimists were\nbusy, though, and with sound finan\ncial conditions as a basis, business\nconditions are excellent in Detroit\nbecause Detroit believes in herself.\u201d\nMr. Potts gave his hearers no op\nportunity to forget the fact that ad\nvertising\u2014intelligent advertising\u2014is\nthe most Important factor in busi\nness success outside of the basic\nprinciple of sound financial condi\ntions.\n\u201cConsider Froctor Gamble,\nmakers of Ivory soap,\u201d he said. \u201cA\nfew years ago the company greatly\ncurtailed its advertising. When the\nannual statement was issued that\nyear Proctor Gamble sales had\nsuffered a loss of 40 per cent! They\ndidn\u2019t get it all back over night,\neither. And some merchants try to\nkid themselves into the idea that\n\u2022advertising doesn\u2019t pay. Gentlemen,\nthe solution for better business lies\nANNOUNCEMENTS\nPersonals.\nCARD OF THANKS\u2014We wish to ex\npress our heartfelt thanks to our\nneighbors ani friends for the sympa\nthy and kindness shown us during the\ndenth of our dear wife and mother;\nalso for the beautiful flowers.\nTHOMAS BRYAN\nMR. tND MRS. LEV'l FUNNELL.\n\u2014r-7\u2014\nAUTOMOBILES\nAutomobiles For Sale. 11'\n*OK SALE\u2014 15-passenger bus, all fully\nequipped. Cheap if taken at once. In\nquire Rudy Miller, Riverside Hotel,\nl-:aglo Toinf. 13-t3\n1'UR SAI.E\u2014Harley Davison with side\near. Ask Mr. Martin, Nash Sales\nService Co.. Ill N. Church St. 13-t3\nAutomobile Tires. 14A\nTIRES New and used. Low prim\nTires guaranteed. Linsenmler Tlra\nhop, 222s Lincoln Way West, Misha\nwaka. *-tf\nBUSINESS SERVICE\nBusiness Service Offered. Id\nGOETZ AND SONS\u2014Sanitary plumbing\nand heating; repair work a specialty.\nEstimates cheerfully given. 2001 W. flth\n\u00bbt, l'hone Miall. 2006. 9-t-7.\nVi'oMAN WANTS Cleaning by hour or\nday. 131 W. Broadway. 13-t3\nt i\nPainting\u2014Papering.34\nCARTERS and Dutch boy lead. 100 lbs.,\n$i;|..\u00bb; .TOO lbs.. $13.00; orange shellac,\n$3.30, white $3.73- per gallon. C. F.\nCook, corner Baker and 4t.h eta., Mish\nawaka 1S09. 14-t-f.\nProfessional Services. 37\nSEE ROBERT E. LEE for advanced\nchiropractic service. Formerly of Lee\nit Joeffler, South Bend. Now located\nnt 510 N. Main St., Mishawaka. l\u2019hone\nMlsh. 2048. 9-tf\nEMPLOYMENT\nHelp Wanted\u2014Male. 33\nAN EXPERIENCED collector wanted;\ngood wages, with chance for advance\nment. Julian Goldman Store, 120-8\nLincoln Way West. 15-tl\nSALESMEN Wanted\u2014Resident of Mish\nawaka preferred Belstle Auto Sales Go.,\n210 _S^Main st. Open Evenings. 10-t-3.\nWanted \u2014First-class mechanic; must\nfurnish reference. Inquire South Side\nGarage, till 8. Main. 10-tf\nSituations Wanted\u2014Male. 37\nWANTED\u2014Position as landscape gard\nener by experienced man. Inquire 210\nN. West St., Mishawaka. 13-t3\nMERCHANDISE\nArticles For Sale. 51\n1H\u00bbH SALE\u2014Nearly new bicycle. Cheap\nif taken at once. Inquire 709 Chris\ntyann St. 15-t3\nPEPPERMINT a till for sale; also 25\nlui lb. cans In good condition. E. B.\nByrhit, 14o3 Lincoln way E. Phone\nMishawaka 1306. 14-t-7.\nTELEPHONE your Classified Ads to\nThe Newa-Tlmee:\nFarm And Dairy Products 63\n4\u00ab0 BCSHF.US POTATOES at farm. 4\nmiles northwest of Buchanan. Law\nrence Nelson. Phone 184F3 Buchanan.\n16-t3\nHousehold Goods. 59\nl\u2019UR KALE\u2014Baby carriage and cot. In\nquire 340 W. Sixth St., upstairs. 10-t 1\nFoil SALE Combination golden oa\u00a3\ndesk and bookcase; excellent condl\ntlon. Inquire 00s W. Third St. It}-t2\nFUR SALK\u2014Combination range. In good\ncondition, luquire 130 E. Mishawaka\nAv. 7-tf\nWHITE ENAMEL ga\u00ab raugette for Vale,\nnearly new. Electric washing machine\nused 9 month*. cheap. Leaving city\n\u00abUM E. Mishawaka av. 15-t-t.\nin your own grasp. It is what you\nmake it.\n\"An enthusiastic selling campaign\ncarried to the door of the consumer\nis as necessary for business success\nas sound financial conditions. We\nare all selling something. No man\nwho isn\u2019t can expect to progress fin\nancially.\u201d\nOutlook Excellent.\nSwinging into the theme of his ad\ndress, \"The Business Outlook,\" Mr.\nPotts devoted 'comparatively little\ntime to predictions. As a basis for\nhis statements he cited the foremost\nfinancial experts in the country.\n\u201cNot a single authority disagrees\nwith the fact that finance is sound\ntoday. Money is cheap and plenti\nful apd more money is waiting in\nvestment than ever in history,\u201d thi\nspeaker said. \u201cExcellent conditions\nlie right ahead, all the experts\nagree, and they see no chance for\nprices to drop.\n\u201cThe fundamental of business is\na sound financial structure. This\ncondition prevails today\u2014more so\nthan at any time in the nation's his\ntory. Because statistics show us that\nbusiness runs in cycles of seven\nyears, I look for at least four more\nyears of excellent conditions.\n\u201cThree factors, 1 believe, will\ncontribute to this. The Dawes re\nparations report has been favorably\naccepted; foreign exchange is great\nly improved; and it is probable that\nfederal taxes will be reduced. These\nall will wield a< very favtfra'ble influ\nence on the nation\u2019s business,\u201d Mr.\nPotts concluded.\nINFANT DIES\nMary Julia Schalstreats, 5-months\nold daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Michael\nSchalstreats, R. R. No. 4, New Car\nlisle, died at 7 a. m. Tuesday follow\ning a week\u2019s illness. Funeral ser\nvices are to be held at 2 p. m. to\nday In St. Bavo\u2019s church with Father\nSchockaert officiating. Burial will\nbe in St. Joseph\u2019s cemetery.\nAID SOCIETY MEETS\nThe Ladies\u2019 Aid society of St.\nPeter\u2019s church will hold its regular\nsocial meeting Thursday afternoon\nat the parish hall with Mesdames\nEdmund Melser, Charles Benzol, Roy\nWallick and N. P. Petersen host\nesses in 'charge.\nTO MEET WEDNESDAY.\nThe Ladies\u2019 Aid society of the\nFirst Christian church will meet\nWednesday afternoon at 2:30\no\u2019clock. Every member is urged to\nattend. v\nGood Pocahontas coal for April\ndelivery. $9.00 per ton. City Coal\nYards, Phone, Mish. 372.\nAdv.\u20144tf\nMERCHANDISE\nSeeds, Plants, Fertilizers. 63\nFOR SALE\u2014Horae grown shrubbery.\nDrive out and select your shrubs trom\nthe field. Barberry, Spirea, Privets,\nFruit and Shade trees. Grape Cut\ntings. Prices right. Lakewood Bar\nberry Farm, Eaat Jefferson rd. Phone\nGarfield 46F1. 3tf\nROOMS AND BOARD\nRooms With Board. 67\nROOM AND BOARD\u2014$8 per week, 462\nShort St., Mishawaka._ 16-1\nUOO.M AND BOARD; gentlemen only;\nmodern: located on street car lino;\nreasonable. 506 E. Broadway. 16-t\"\nRooms Without Board. 68\nFOR RENT\u2014Sleeping rooms; suitable\nfor two; one, large roorj., twin beds,\nbath, hot water day and night; half\nblock off Ball Band. ZT> N. Main St\n1543\nRooms For Housekeeping. 69\nEUR RENT\u20142 large rooms, in modern\nhomo, furnished or unfurnished. In\nquire 427 Calhoun St.1243\nEUR RENT\u20143 furnished rooms: ground\nfloor: private entrance. 830 E. Mish\nawaka av.14-t-2.\nFttR RENT\u20143 unfurnished room! with\ngarden, also sleeping room; adults\nonly, 816 E. Grove st,144-7.\nFOR RENT\u2014Three upstairs rooms for\nlight housekeeping. Phone Mish. ISM.\n3321 .j W. Mishawaka Av._ 16-tl\nTWO FURNISHED housekeeping*rooms;\nfirst door, at 313 W. First. Phone\nMish. 10.11.13-13\nTWO FURNISHED rooms for light\nhousekeeping; all modern. Also gar\nage. Phone Mlsh. 3050; 8-tf\nTWO MODERN furnished light house\nkeeping rooms: private entrance; no\nchildren. 113 W. Seventh St. Phone\nMish. 1507 14-17\n\nREAL ESTATE FOR RENT\nApartments and Flats. 74\nFOR RENT\u20145-room modern flat to re\nliable people. Inquire at C14 E. Mish\nawaka Av. 16-t.';\nTHREE UNFURNISHED rooms; close\nin, on south side; garden and garage.\nReasonable rent.\nMASON L. PETRO\nSuite 7 and 8, Farmers and Merch\nants Bank Bldg.. Mishawaka.\nPhone Mish. 1S3,154f\nTHREE unfurnished rooms for rent In\nquire 714 E. Fourth st.144-2.\nSIX room apartment; upstairs: modern:\nIS per month. Inquire 811 E. Battel]\nst. 144-3.\nBusiness Places For Rent. 75\nFOR RENT\u2014Store building with living\nrooms; furnished if desired. Inquire\nEd Neddo. Twin Branch. ll-t-3.\nRouses For Remit 77\nBUNGALOW for rent. 136 Borley Av.;\nelectric lights.13-tl\nFOR RENT\u2014Furnished cottage. Inquire\n330 South West St. 16-tl\nFOR RENT\u2014Modern lionise. 1310 W.\u2018\nSixth St. Call Garfield l-F-3. 1343\nFOR RENT\u20143-room cottage, with gar\nage, on Somerset St. $35. Seymour\nJansen. Phone Misli. 1373. 14-tf\nOffices and Desk Room. 78\nFURNISHED OFFICE ROOM and desk\nspare in modern office building. Tele\nphone, light and beat furnished. Ad\ndress Box A, News-Times, Mishawaka.\n15-tf\nREAL ESTATE FOR SALE\nFarms and Land For Sale 83\nFOR SALE 3-1* ucres, 4-room house,\nlarge chicken coop, some mint and\nstrawberries. Five miles south, one\nmile east. Inquire 217 N. Spring.\n13-t2\nHouses For Sale. 84 I\nVV. 7TH STREET NEAR LOGAN Five\nrooms and bath. All modern bunga\nlow. Nearing completion. Reason\nable priced on terms within your\nreach. Colpaert 'Realty Corporation\n126-8 Lincoln Way West.13-tf\nHot SKS .vested in ail parts of tllr ei.\nI lire Geo. Walton, over Wlnejr'a Stor\nPhone Blah. 090\u20141593. \u00ab-u\n\nNATIONAL GUARD\nUNIT MOBILIZED\nBY SECRET ORDER\nLocal Infantry Company\nReady to Entrain\u201470\nMen Affected.\nCompany I, 152d infantry, Misha\nwaka national guard unit, was ready\nfor war Monday. Seventy officers and\nenlisted men were unaer arms await\ning orders to entrain for a mobiliza\ntion point which has not been re\nvealed.\nSecret orders were received by\nCapt. C. B. Hartwick' at 2 p. jn.\nMonday from the commander of the\nFifth Corps Area calling for mobil\nization of the local unit by 7 p. m.\nTuesday. The men were to be held\nin readiness to entrain immediately,\norder for which was expected Tues\nday afternoon.\nNo information was given as to\nthe movement of the men, but it\nwas known that every guard unit in\nthe Fifth Corps Area received sim\nilar orders.\"\nAt the Company I regular drill\nperiod Monday night full field equip\nment, ordnance and ammunition was\nissued, less than six hours after re\nceipt of the order by Capt. Hart\nwick. -i\nDuring Monday evening\u2019s manu\nvers at guard headquarters here\nseven officers and enlisted men were\ndecorated with marksmanship\nmedals which were qualified for at\nthe regimental shoot held last July\n27 at Camp Knox.\nFirst Lieut. Fred F. Longfellow,\nwith' 298 points out of a possible\n?00, qualified for the bronze expert\nmedal. Capt. C. B. Hartwick, with\n291 out of a possible 300, qualified as\nsharpshooter.\nEnlisted men receiving marksman\nmedals for scoring more than 240\npoints out of a possible 300 in the\nregimental shoot, together with\ntheir scores follow:\nSergt. Donald E. Maxham, 273;\nCorporal Edward Wygant, 261; Cor\nporal bjldon E. Miller, 256; Private\nFirst Class Roland D. Hupp, 241;\nPrivate John S. Dunfee, 251.\nF. A. M. ATTENTION\nMishawaka lodge 130 F. A. M.\ncalled meeting Wednesday evening\nat 7:30. Work in fc. A. degree.\nM. W. HJJNSBERGER, W. M.\nWALTER MICHAEL, Secy.\nAdvt. 15tl.\nREAL ESTATE FOR SALE\nHouses For Sale. 84\nDON'T PAY KENT\nBUY A HOME.\n$200 DOWN.\nS. Spring Street Large lot. AH\nnew properties. We have now under\nconstruction a number of attractive\nfour-room bungalows. These homes\nare not of the garage /it shanty type.\nThey are now two fiearly completed\nand will be ready for occupancy in\nabout one week. Electric fixtures.\nNeatly finished Interior. First-class\nconstruction throughout. Basement\nunder en'ire house. Porch across\nfront. Pay 1200 down, the balance in\nmonthly payments like rent.\nCOLPAERT REALTY CORPORATION\n12<i-S Lincoln Way West.\nOpen evenings 7 to 8. 13-tf\nEAST END\u2014Four rooms and bath. All\nmodern. Immediate possession. Large\nlot. Two blocks from Lincoln Way\nand new high school. Restricted ad\ndition. $400 down, balance monthly.\nPhone Colpnert Realty Corp., Mish.\n_118L13-tf\nFOR SALE\u2014All-modern 0-room house,\nE. Lawrence St. French doors, screen\ned porches. Terms. 7-room house,\nEast 3rd St., large lot, $4,000. Terms.\n4-room bungalow, lot. 30x130, $3,200.\nE-Z Te-rms. 5-room bungalow, partly\nmodern, $3,400, Terms. 8-room, all\nmodern home, close in, double garage.\nA real buy. 8-room house on paved\nstreet, $4,000. Terms. 4-room house,\n$1,130. Terms. New 4-room houses\nwith acres or half acres, electric lights.\nInside city limits in Maple-Hurst\nPlace. Several 3-room houses, $50 to\n$100 down. Call\nGEO. F. EBKRHART SONS\nFarmers Bank Bldg.\nPhone Mish. 270. 14-tf\nFOR SALE\u20143 room cottage, lathe land\nplastered. Vj acre of ground, $H500,\neasy terms. Seymour Jansen. Phone\nMishawaka 1272. lltf.\nFOR SALE.\nNearly new five-room bungalow,\nclose to Mishawaka Av. West; all mod\nern. Price $4,500. Will take in used\ncar as part payment.\nNew modern six-room house; three\nbed rooms, and four closets, double\ngarage, close to Mishawaka Av. West.\nImmediate possession. Price $7,800.\n$2,000 cash required.\nGood lot with okl house of six\nrooms and bath room, also garage, on\nEast Fourth St. Price $1,050.\nWe have four or five modern five\nroom bungalows. Prices and terms\nreasonable.\n1H acre tract near Station 7, on\nLincoln Way East. $1,000. $350 cash\nrequired.\nFine corner lot on West Broadway;\nimprovements in and paid for. $050\nAbout half cash required.\nIdeal building lot on Pleasant St.,\nlVa blocks from Logan, with side and\nrear alley. Terms $700, or $650 cash,\nplus sewer assessment.\nSTARK REALTY COMPANY,\nRealtors\n126 Lincoln Way East. 13-16\nNEW BUNGALOW\n$300 DOWN\nNew and strictly modern bungalow.\nContaining five rooms and completely\nequipped bath. Basement under entire\nhouse. Floor drain. Connections for\nlaundry tubs. Combination water heat\ner. Sink and bulk in cupboard in kitch\nen. Double floors over entire house.\nSolid oak floors in living room and\ndining room. Book ease eolonades. In\nterior neatly finished in light oak. Two\nnice bed rooms with spacious closet'\nin each. Linen closet In hallway. Bath\nfinished In white enamel. Porch across\nfront. Good sized lot. Close in on South\nside.\nCOLPAERT REALTY CORPORATION\n126-8 Lincoln way West.\nPhone Mish. 11S1.\n10-t-f.\nSPECIAL bargains, two 4-room bouses,\nall finished and ready to move in;\nmust be sold at once, so don\u2019t delay;\nterms, $50 cash Prices $1,900 and $2,000.\nM L. Petro Phone Miab 183 \u00a3ltf\n$200 DOWN\u2014New four-room house; good\nlocation. 14th St. Pay for It like rent.\nColpaert Realty Corp. Phone Mish.\n1181. 6-tf\nI/>ts For Sale,_ 85\nFOR SALE\u20142 lots. Home st.; 2 lots.\nI/>gan st.; cheap If taken at once. 205\nUeddich \u00abt. lAt-3,\nPOLICE AND\nCITY COURT\nAnother automobile driver fell\nvictim Tuesday to the Mishawaka\npolice department war on traffic\nlaw violators when Jesse Bayam, 20,\n1010 N. Merrifleld av., was fined 91\nand costs amounting to $10 for\nseeding on E. Mishawaka av.. Mon\npay evening.\nThe case of James Nichols,\ncharged with assault to commit a\nfelony after alleged threats to kill\nAlex Csallo,; was continued until\nWednesday. Nichols was held In\nthe city jail because of his Inability\nto furnish $1,000 bond.\nJudgment for $205 was granted\nCharles L. Metzger in his suit against\nJohn A. May in City court Tues\nday. The judgment went by de\nfault as May failed to appear when\nthe case was called!'\nJohn Barron, It. R. No. 1, Os*\nceola, was arrested by Mishawaka\npolice Tuesday on a charge of pass\ning a street car while it was stopped\nto discharge passengers. He was\nreleased on $100 bond for appear\nance in city court this morning.\nCENTURY\nAll the glitter and glamor of\nMonte Carlo are depicted in \u201cFool\nish Wives,\u201d the record-breaking\nphotodrama now being shown at the\nCentury theater. At enormous cost\nthe principal buildings of the Med\niterranean resort were duplicated at\nUniversal City, Cal., for the produc\ntion of the film. The interiors of\nthe famous Hall of Chance are\nshown with remarkable fidelity, as\nwell as the smaller and more Bo\nhemian gaming salons with their\ncrowds of adventurers and adventur\nesses.\nWOODJMEjN\u2019S CIRCUS\nWho will be Miss Mishawaka?\nWho will be crotyned queen? Who\nwill be the choice girl of this city?\nWill she be a blonde or brunette,\nor will she be sixteen or sixty\nThis will be the question heard\ndaily on the streets of this city\nduring the next three weeks prior\nto the coming of the big Modern\nWoodmen\u2019s circus that is being\nbrought here starting May 3rd and\nlasting seven days. This is to be\nthe first outdoor event of the year.\nThS Modern Woodmen are conduct\n,ing a popularity contest to deter\nmine just who will be the lucky\ngirl to obtain this trip to Holly\nCENTURY\nErich Von Stroheim\n\"The man you lore to hate\u201d\nIn\nthe ten reel, million dollar feature\n\u201cFoolish Wives\u201d\nPersons Ioohing for thrills and\nrealism will hare their fill in this\npicture. The scene concerning the\nTT. s. Marine on leave at Monte\nCarlo will make your blood boil\nwith rage and later will bring\ntears and applause.\nAlso\nGnod old\nHarold Lloyd\n\u201cBliss\u201d\nA Pathe Comedy\nPRICES\nAdults\u201420c\nCHILDREN\u201410c\nP\nL\nE\nPHOTO\n\u2022PLAYS\nNow Showing!\n\u201cTHE GIRL\nI LOVED\u201d\nThe heart story\nof a great poet\nvisualized by a\ngreat actor\u2014\nCHAS. RAY\n\u2014Added\u2014\n\u201cTHE NEW\nSHERIFF\u201d\nPlenty of Fun\nFast and\nFurious!\nAlso Latest\nREVIEW\nNow\nIs the time to place your or\nder for Easter Flowers. Deliv\nery when you wish. Our lilies\nI this year are the most beauti\nj ful ever, and will add the real\nEaster touch to your home.\nPhone Mish. 13 Today\nEDGEWATER\nFloral Place\n209 W. Cedar St\nS. W. SPRAGUE\nUNDERTAKER\nAmbulance\u2014 Lady Assistant\n202 North Main Streak\nPhone Mish. 100\n\u2022t:\nwood, Cal., absolutely free of charge.\nThe circus being brought to this\ncity by the Woodmen will consist\nof 20 feature circus acts that are\nseen nowhere but under the big\nwhite tops of the large circuses that\ntravel the road In the summer sea\nson.\nOffices have been opened and are\nnow in full blast at 114 S. Main\nst., where the committee is work\ning to make this circus a surcess.\nWhen you purchase a ticket, Vrlte\nthe name of the girl of your choice\non the attached stub and bring it\nto the circus headquarters at once\nand thereby cast 50 votes In the\npopularity contest.\nBUILDING PERMITS.\nGeorge Eberhart, house, Maple\nhurst rd., $2,200.\nStuff Sparrows for Roy Jewell,\naddition, 927 W. Broadway, $614.\nC. W. Cuthbert, two houses, N.\nMerrifleld rd., $1000 each.\nMcKenna-Bradford-Cuthbert, four\nhouses, Marion st., $1,200 each.\nHenry Koehler, garage, N. Byrkit\nav., $100.\nRose Linski, garage, 414 1-2 S.\nLaurel, $118.'\nG. B. Moyer for Charles Part\nridge, house, \"State st., $3,000.\nCurtis Hanna, garage, Lafayette\nst., $200.'\nCLASS ENTERTAINED.\nThe Live Wire class of the Im\nmanuel Baptist church was enter\ntained Monday evening at the home\nof William Power. 1320 N. Benton\nst. A short business session was\nheld after which contests were en\njoyed. The next meeting will be at\nthe home of Gerald Ritter, N. Forest\nav., April 28th.\nGet your Easter Marcell at the O.\nX. Barber shop. Phone Mishawaka\n2769. Advt. 15t4.\nHARTMAN REESE\nSON\nBulk Garden Seed and Feed\n226 NORTH MAIN ST.\nPrompt Delivery Mish. 207\nSent to You on Free Trial!\nTHE GRAND PRIZE\nDuring Spring Housecleaning\nThe manufacturers have authorized us to make this\ngreat free educational offer to you to prove the merits\nof the Eureka. Upon request we will deliver to your\ndoor on five days\u2019 free cleaning trial a new Eureka.\nUse it without cost just when you need a cleaner the\nmost\u2014during housecleaning.\nThis Free Trial Offer Expires May 17\nOnly a limited number of cleaners are to be\nloaned. Don\u2019t pay a man to beat your rugs. Use\nthe Eureka instead. Then if you decide to buy\nyou can pay.\na j ij r i\\ Balahce Easy\nOnly *4== Down Monthly Payments\nMake this five-day test at our expense. See\nhow thoroughly the Eureka will clean the entire\nhouse. This free loan offer enables you to prove\nits wonderful merits before you buy and our\neasy payment plan allows you to pay for it\nat the rate of a few cents a day.\nPhone, Call or Send Coupon Today.\nEUREKA APPLIANCE COMPANY\nAt the\nNorth Side Electric Shop\n607 North Main St.\nPhone Mish. 470\nFree Trial\nOffer\nSet Your Name and Address\nHere.\nSend me details of your free\ntrial offer\nName..\nAddress\nNo Profit Sale\nPianos, Player Pianos, Phonographs\nTHREE DAYS ONLY\nThursday, Friday and Saturday\nI _ N\nWe find ourselves over-stocked with a number of fine used and demonstrator Pianos, Phonographs and\nPlayer Pianos. All Must be Moved at a Sacrifice.\nAll Must Be Moved at a Sacrifice\nThese instruments must go, regardless of price to make room for new goods. Our terms and prices will\nsurprise you.\nNO PROFIT SALE\nYou can now buy a good Piano or Phonograph at little more than actual manufacturer\u2019s cost. Look at\nthese prices, then come into the store and see for yourself*\n1\nPIANOS-$105.00, $125.00, $150.00, $375.00,\n$175.00, $250.00, $75.00\nPHONOGRAPHS-$ 15.00, $45.00, $59.00, $67.00,\n$55.00, $65.00, $80.00, $75.00, $90.00,\n$53.00, $75.00, $28.00\nTERMS\n$5.00 puts any Phonograph in your home.\n$10.00 will deliver a Fine Piano.\nV\nDON\u2019T DELAY\u2014COME IN TODAY!\nCOMPLETE MUSIC STORES\n109 NORTH MAIN STREET\nMISHAWAKA, 1ND.","height":"31456","width":"23648"}}
